OL,3,CJenrick asks top civil servant to
OL,4,Cinvestigate Attorney General
OL,6,FMr Jenrick claimed the matters "raise
OL,7,Fserious questions about the management
OL,8,Fof potential conflicts of interest at
OL,9,Fthe highest levels of Government legal
OL,10,Fservice" and asked that the Cabinet
OL,11,FSecretary "investigate these matters
OL,12,Fand revert to me as a matter of
OL,13,Furgency".
OL,15,FA Government spokesperson said: "There
OL,16,Fare well-established rules governing
OL,17,Fministerial interests and conflicts,
OL,18,Fand as Robert Jenrick's own letter
OL,19,Fmakes clear, the Attorney General has
OL,20,Fproperly declared interests from his
OL,21,Fprevious role.
